last_episode_to_air.name: The Westminster Human Show
last_episode_to_air.overview: Chaos brings the Higgins family closer together as Godcat and Devilcat face their final challenge: making humans go against their own nature.

name: Exploding Kittens
overview: It's the ultimate fight between good and evil when God and his nemesis, the spawn of Satan, are sent to Earth to live with humans — as talking cats.
tagline: God and the Devil. Trapped in cat bodies.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Sent to Earth in the body of a cat, God moves in with the dysfunctional Higgins family, then takes game night in a wildly different direction.

episodes.name: Tartar Recall
episodes.overview: Greta goes to work with Marv, and Godcat and Devilcat watch the movie "Armageddon." Travis and Abbie follow Aidan to Heck — not Hell.

episodes.name: Shane & Chugger's
episodes.overview: To show Travis they really love him, Abbie and Marv plan a last minute half-birthday rager. Godcat summons the cherubs to see the wonders of Earth.

episodes.name: Emotions Are Hard
episodes.overview: Greta enters a rocket-building competition sponsored by billionaire Jefflon Bezmusk. Meanwhile, Travis moves out — and the cats get inside Marv's head.

episodes.name: No Regrets
episodes.overview: Devilcat takes Godcat as her plus-one to a wedding in Hell. Travis goes back in time to undo his biggest regret — but changing the past has consequences.

episodes.name: The Town with No Internet
episodes.overview: Devilcat takes Abbie and the kids on a hellish road trip to Halcyon Springs to meet her long-lost mother. Godcat helps Marv ask for a promotion.

episodes.name: SeaWorld Is Hell
episodes.overview: Devilcat and Godcat go to SeaWorld, Marv drags Abbie to a "work thing" aboard a corporate blimp, and Greta helps Travis track down a troll.

episodes.name: Let the Games Begin
episodes.overview: It's good vs. evil as the cats compete in the God Games for control of Heaven and Hell. Travis' friends turn against him. Marv inherits a mess at work.
